  "text": "Cancer survivors have ongoing, unmet, needs. Up to 10 years after diagnosis, those patients with breast and colorectal cancer are more likely to visit their GP than people without a cancer diagnosis [CITATION_1] . Cancer survivors can spend significant amounts of time in hospital many years after diagnosis [CITATION_2] . With increasing survival, it is likely that more people will suffer from consequences of their cancer treatment in later years.",
